request.description:
`GET /users/{user_id}` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Retrieve the full profile of a single admin user identified by UUID.  Returns **404** if the user does not exist.

**Path params:** `user_id`

`PATCH /users/{user_id}` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Partially update an admin user's `full_name` and/or `district_scope`.  Only the fields present in the request body are changed (PATCH semantics).  An audit entry is written for every update.

**Path params:** `user_id`

`PATCH /roles/{role_id}` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Replace the `name` and `permissions` array of an existing role.  All users assigned this role immediately inherit the new permissions.

**Path params:** `role_id`

`POST /sessions/{session_id}:revoke` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Mark a session as revoked by setting its `revoked_at` timestamp.  Any token associated with that session will no longer be considered valid by session-aware middleware.

**Path params:** `session_id`

`POST /districts` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Register a new administrative district.  

The `code` field must be unique across all districts.  Optionally supply a `boundary_ref` (GeoJSON reference string) for map integration.  An audit entry is written on success.

`GET /districts/{district_id}` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Retrieve the full record of a single district using its UUID primary key.  Returns **404** if the district does not exist.

**Path params:** `district_id`

`PATCH /districts/{district_id}` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Update one or more of a district's mutable fields: `code`, `name`, or `boundary_ref`.  Omitted fields are left unchanged (PATCH semantics).  An audit entry is written recording the field-level diff.

**Path params:** `district_id`

`POST /polling-stations` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Register a new polling station.  

The `district_id` must reference an existing district — returns **400** if not found.  The station is created with status `not_open` by default.  An audit entry is written on success.

`GET /polling-stations/{station_id}` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Retrieve the full record of a single polling station using its UUID primary key.  Returns **404** if the station does not exist.

**Path params:** `station_id`

`PATCH /polling-stations/{station_id}` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Update one or more mutable fields of a polling station: `name`, `lat`, `lon`, `opens_at`, `closes_at`.  Omitted fields are left unchanged (PATCH semantics).  Use `:open` and `:close` custom actions to change the station's operational status.

**Path params:** `station_id`

`POST /polling-stations/{station_id}:open` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Set the station's status to `online`, indicating that it is open and accepting voters.  An audit entry is written with action `STATUS_SYNCED`.  Returns **404** if the station does not exist.

**Path params:** `station_id`

`POST /polling-stations/{station_id}:close` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Set the station's status to `offline`, indicating that voting has ended at this station.  An audit entry is written with action `STATUS_SYNCED`.  Returns **404** if the station does not exist.

**Path params:** `station_id`

`GET /districts/{district_id}/stations` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Returns all polling stations belonging to the given district.  Returns **404** if the district does not exist.

**Path params:** `district_id`

`POST /officers` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Register a new field officer.  

Optionally assign the officer to a `team` and a district via `assigned_district_id`.  The `assigned_district_id` is not validated against the districts table at creation time — ensure you pass a valid UUID if district scoping is required.

`GET /officers/{officer_id}` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Retrieve the full record of a single field officer using their UUID primary key.  Returns **404** if the officer does not exist.

**Path params:** `officer_id`

`PATCH /officers/{officer_id}` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Update one or more of a field officer's mutable fields: `name`, `team`, or `assigned_district_id`.  Omitted fields are left unchanged (PATCH semantics).  Returns **404** if the officer does not exist.

**Path params:** `officer_id`

`POST /voters` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Create a new voter record in the registry.  

Both `district_id` and `polling_station_id` must reference existing geography records — returns **400** if either is missing.  The voter is created with status `registered` and no biometric template.

`GET /voters/by-token/{voter_token}` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Retrieve a voter record using the unique `voter_token` printed on their voter card.  This is the primary lookup used at registration desks before biometric enrolment.

**Path params:** `voter_token`

`GET /voters/{voter_id}` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Retrieve the full profile of a voter by their internal UUID primary key.  Use `GET /voters/by-token/{voter_token}` when you only have the voter card token.

**Path params:** `voter_id`

`POST /voters/{voter_id}:archive` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Move a voter to `archived` status.  Archived voters are excluded from active registry counts and cannot participate in elections.  Typically used after a duplicate merge operation (the loser record is archived).

**Path params:** `voter_id`

`POST /voters/{voter_id}:restore` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Reset a voter's status back to `registered`, reversing a previous block or archive action.  The restored voter regains the ability to be verified and to vote.

**Path params:** `voter_id`

`GET /voters:export` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Download the complete voter registry as a CSV file.  The response streams a `text/csv` attachment named `voters.csv`.  An audit entry is written recording who exported the data and when.
**Query params:** `format`

`GET /voters/{voter_id}/verifications` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Returns all biometric verification attempts recorded for a specific voter, ordered newest-first.  Includes result, confidence, liveness, and timestamp for each.

**Path params:** `voter_id`

`PUT /biometrics/enroll` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Replaces the existing face biometric template for a voter with a new one.  

The pipeline is identical to `POST /biometrics/enroll` but deletes the previous template before storing the new one.  A `BIOMETRIC_RE_ENROLLED` audit entry is written.  Use this when a voter's face has changed significantly (e.g. after surgery or a long time since original enrolment).

`GET /verifications/{attempt_id}` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Retrieve the full record of a single verification attempt by its UUID.  Returns the complete decision breakdown including face score, confidence, liveness, flags, and explanation.

**Path params:** `attempt_id`

`POST /fraud/cases` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Raise a fraud case manually (as opposed to auto-creation by the deduplication pipeline).  

A unique case ID is generated in the format `FR-XXXXXX` using a random hex suffix.  An audit entry is written with action `CASE_CREATED`.

`GET /fraud/cases/{case_id}` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Retrieve the full details of a single fraud case by its string ID (e.g. `FR-A1B2C3`).  Returns **404** if the case does not exist.

**Path params:** `case_id`

`POST /fraud/cases/{case_id}:dismiss` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Mark a fraud case as `dismissed` — indicating an investigator has reviewed it and determined it is not a genuine fraud.  Sets `resolution = dismissed` and records `resolved_at`.  An audit entry is written.

**Path params:** `case_id`

`POST /fraud/cases/{case_id}:escalate` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Mark a fraud case as `escalated` — forwarding it to a higher authority for further action.  Sets `resolution = escalated` and records `resolved_at`.  An audit entry is written.

**Path params:** `case_id`

`GET /duplicates/{match_id}` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Retrieve the full record of a single `DuplicateMatch` by its UUID.  Returns the two voter IDs, similarity score, status, and resolution metadata.

**Path params:** `match_id`

`POST /anomalies` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Create an anomaly signal manually (e.g. from an external monitoring rule or script).  

A unique anomaly ID is generated in the format `ANO-XXXXXX`.  An audit entry is written with action `ANOMALY_CREATED`.

`GET /anomalies/{anomaly_id}` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Retrieve the full record of a single anomaly signal by its string ID.  Returns the same field set as the list endpoint but for one specific signal.

**Path params:** `anomaly_id`

`DELETE /anomalies/{anomaly_id}` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Permanently delete an anomaly signal.  An audit entry with action `ANOMALY_RESOLVED` is written before deletion.  Returns **204 No Content** on success.

**Path params:** `anomaly_id`

`POST /anomalies/{anomaly_id}:acknowledge` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Mark an anomaly signal as `acknowledged` — indicating that an operator has seen it and is investigating.  The signal remains visible (`is_live` unchanged) until explicitly muted or resolved.

**Path params:** `anomaly_id`

`POST /anomalies/{anomaly_id}:mute` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Silence an anomaly signal by setting its status to `muted` and `is_live = false`.  Muted signals are hidden from live dashboards but remain in the database for audit purposes.

**Path params:** `anomaly_id`

`GET /audit/entries/{entry_id}` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Retrieve one audit entry by its UUID primary key.  The entry includes its SHA-256 `entry_hash` and the `prev_hash` of the preceding entry, allowing manual chain verification.

**Path params:** `entry_id`

`GET /keys/health` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Returns a summary of every registered encryption key including its current version number and algorithm.  This endpoint simulates a Hardware Security Module (HSM) health probe.  

An audit entry is written with action `HSM_HEALTHCHECK` so that health probes are traceable in the immutable audit log.  Use this endpoint from monitoring scripts to verify key availability and rotation state.

`GET /keys` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Returns all encryption key records registered in the system, ordered by creation date.  

Each record stores key metadata only — the actual key material is managed by the HSM and never returned by this API.  Use `current_version` to track rotation history.

`GET /keys/{key_id}` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Retrieve the metadata record for a single encryption key by its UUID primary key.  Returns **404** if the key record does not exist.

**Path params:** `key_id`

`POST /ai/rebuild-index` — Auth: Bearer {{access_token}}

Rebuilds the FAISS 1:N index from the AES-256-GCM encrypted embeddings stored in the database (original images are not needed — only the embeddings are required, and they are persisted).  

Each template's `faiss_id` is reassigned to its new index position, repairing any drift between the in-memory index and the database — the usual cause of broken 1:N de-duplication after a restart.  Use `GET /ai/status` to inspect index size.
